race.description: Become A Member Today Class 1 Handicap
race.comment: Interesting race with a couple of last start debut winners clashing. Leaning to YACHT GIRL (7) who hasn't appeared since comfortably scoring over 1100m at Armidale when lining up for this first time back in February. Won a recent trial at Scone and looks to have come on over the break. Race favourite SOMERTON SMART (4) is the danger after he cruised to victory on debut over this distance at Coonabarabran 18 days ago. Four subsequent winners have emerged from that race to add merit to the performance. Wide gate the only negative. BOLT AWAY NOW (3) returns from a five-month spell. Best form is over a bit further but a strong trial win at Tamworth last week suggests he is ready to run a big race. SETHNIQUE (6) collected his maiden win last start at the eighth attempt. Needs to go up a level but a top four finish is on the cards. INVINCIBLE WHIP (2) has been about the mark of late and is worth throwing in the exotic bets.
